#Text=Space Shuttle Atlantis lands in California
#Text=Friday , June 22 , 2007

#Text=The Space Shuttle Atlantis has performed a successful landing at Edwards Air Force Base in California , completing STS-117 , a troubled but successful mission to upgrade the International Space Station ( ISS ) .
#Text=The mission had a total duration of 13 days , 20 hours and 11 minutes , much longer than originally intended due to a mission extension and a missed landing opportunity .

#Text=The landing in California is the result of the latest in a string of difficulties for the mission , as poor weather forced Atlantis first to postpone its landing at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida , then to cancel it altogether , opting instead to land in California .
#Text=NASA had previously expressed their desire to avoid a landing in California if possible due to logistical difficulties that would be caused by the diversion .
#Text=Atlantis will now be flown back to Florida on the back of a modified Boeing 747 at a cost of around US$ 1 million .
#Text=The flight is expected to begin next Thursday and will take at least a day or two from then .

#Text=According to officials at the Kennedy Space Center , the delay is already accounted for as a previously identified possibility as part of plans for the next Atlantis mission , scheduled for departure on October 20 , again for ISS construction work .

#Text=During this mission , the Atlantis crew added the 17.5 ton S3/S4 Truss , the second of the trusses on the starboard side , as well as adding its associated energy systems , including the unfurling a set of solar arrays with a 240 foot tip-to-tip length .
#Text=The arrays will generate power for European and Japanese science laboratories set to be added to the ISS at a later date .
#Text=During the same mission , another solar array was folded up to allow the truss it is mounted to to be relocated later this year .

#Text=The shuttle also left crewmember Clay Anderson at the ISS and returned with ISS crewmember Sunita Williams , who earlier set the record for female space endurance during her latest ISS mission .
#Text=Although successful , there were numerous problems during the mission .

#Text=A computer failure in the Russian segments of the ISS almost forced the shuttle 's mission to be extended and left the ISS struggling to maintain thrusters , oxygen generation , carbon dioxide scrubber , and other environmental control systems , and relying on Atlantis to help .
#Text=Officials even looked at the possibility of an unprecedented emergency evacuation of the ISS , although astronauts were ultimately able to repair the systems .

#Text=Other concerns included hail damage , which delayed the mission 's launch ; damage to the thermal blanket , which required a spacewalk to repair ; and discovery of unidentified debris shortly after Atlantis docked with the ISS .
#Text=The mission had to be extended by two days in order to give astronauts time to repair the damaged heat-protection equipment .
#Text=NASA officials held an emergency meeting Wednesday while engineers confirmed that they thought the repair would withstand the rigors of re-entry with the Earth 's atmosphere .
